Require dependencies for ubantu and PHP
--------------------------------------
First of all install chrome, sublime, skype then go for PHP:

https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-install-sublime-text-3-on-ubuntu-18-04/

----------------------------------------


sudo apt-get update


sudo apt-get install apache2


sudo apt-get install mysql-server


sudo apt-get update
sudo apt -y install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php
sudo apt-get update

sudo apt -y install php7.4

sudo apt-get install -y php7.4-{bcmath,bz2,intl,gd,mbstring,mysql,zip,common}


sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install phpmyadmin php-mbstring php-gettext

Some points that we need to remember at the time fo phpmyadmin installation.
For the server selection, choose apache2.
Select yes when asked whether to use dbconfig-common to set up the database
You will be prompted for your database administratorâ€™s password
You will then be asked to choose and confirm a password for the phpMyAdmin application itself
